VNada Bharati presented Radha Sarangapani&#8217;s concert as as part of its traditional concert series at Mahati Hall, DD Colony. Radha presentedragasfor all importantkirtanas.She opened the show with rare a Vachaspativarnamof Patnam and went for Begada forVallabha Nayakasyaof Deekshitar. Shyamasatry&#8217;sMariverefigured in Ananda Bhairavi.Papanasam Sivan&#8217;s rare composition was her choice in Gourimanohari. The main essay of her concert was Khambhoji and she packed it with goodsangatis. K.Rajan on violin and Srinivas Gopalan on mridangam lent even support.A percussionist originally, Shyam Kumar is now a laudable vocalist too. He began with Kalyani aditala varnam-Vanajakshi.He then essayed brieflyragaMayamalavagowla in which he presented the popular numberTulasidalamulacheof Thyagaraja.Inkevarunnaruin Sahana was a rare number from him.Theswarasin it were breezy.Sudha Madhurya Bhashanain Sindhunamakriya was comparatively a fast number. After Thyagaraja&#8217;sNee Chittamuin Misrachaputalam, he chose Keeravani as the major melody of his concert and presented in it Thyagaraja&#8217;sKaligiyunte.K.Rajan on violin and Srinivas Gopalan on mridangam lent good support to the vocalist.
